<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FD67BEFEFCD54658" box="[743,806,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
wide at segment 10 for ~65 segments. Body deep pink in life (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FF4BBD22FEC3467F" box="[203,304,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-25@24.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. A—dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). B—ventral view of holotype, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). C—live dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). D—whole body, paratype (SIO-BIC A4651). E—drawing of compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). F—dorsal cirri, holotype (SIO- BIC A13418). G—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479953/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 17C</figureCitation>
). Body brown/orange with numerous dark pigmentation speckles in preserved (formalin/ethanol) state (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FF20BD46FEB84620" box="[160,331,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-25@24.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. A—dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). B—ventral view of holotype, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). C—live dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). D—whole body, paratype (SIO-BIC A4651). E—drawing of compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). F—dorsal cirri, holotype (SIO- BIC A13418). G—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479953/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 17A, B, D</figureCitation>
). Lobe-like prostomium; nuchal organs not visible (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FC0FBD46FC0B4623" box="[911,1016,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Anterior dorsal edge of prostomium with paired cylindrical antennae ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FD92BD6AFD9A46C4" box="[530,617,619,646]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FD2FBD6AFCCA46C4" box="[687,825,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18A, D</figureCitation>
). Paired palps ventral to antennae, similar in shape and length to antennae (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FEF5BD8EFE2D46EB" box="[373,478,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Segment one dorsally fused to prostomium, following segments clearly demarcated (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FF20BDB2FEF9468F" box="[160,266,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Pair of elongated dorsal cirri [tentacular cirri] on each of segments 1 (~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FBCDBDB2FB46468C" box="[1101,1205,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
long), 2 (~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FAB5BDB2FA6E468C" box="[1333,1437,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
long) and 3 (~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FEBDBDD6FE6B46B0" box="[317,408,727,754]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long) (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FE6FBDD6FDA946B3" box="[495,602,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). All elongated dorsal cirri cirriform, tapering distally. Pair of elongated ventral cirri on segment 2 ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FE5FBDFAFDBB4754" box="[479,584,763,790]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FD17BDFAFCF04757" box="[663,771,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Bulbous, rounded dorsal cirri ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FB07BDFAFB034754" box="[1159,1264,763,790]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
long begin on segment 4 continuing posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FD9DBC1EFD5B477B" box="[541,680,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18A, C</figureCitation>
). Conical, tapering ventral cirri ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FBA4BC1EFB8F4778" box="[1060,1148,799,826]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long begin on segment 3 continuing posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FE1FBC42FDF4471F" box="[415,519,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Ventral cilia bands present (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FCD2BC42FC49471F" box="[850,954,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Parapodia uniramous, notopodial chaetae absent; neuropodium with central fascicle containing ~5–8 compound chaetae; one simple emergent acicula (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FAEABC66FEF747E7" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-25@24.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. A—dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). B—ventral view of holotype, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). C—live dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). D—whole body, paratype (SIO-BIC A4651). E—drawing of compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). F—dorsal cirri, holotype (SIO- BIC A13418). G—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479953/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Figs 17E, F, G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FE8FBC8AFECD47E7" box="[271,318,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">18F</figureCitation>
). Compound chaetal shaft cylindrical; thin, flattened pointed blade extended from curved joint (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FAEFBC8AFF3B478B" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-25@24.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. A—dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). B—ventral view of holotype, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). C—live dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). D—whole body, paratype (SIO-BIC A4651). E—drawing of compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). F—dorsal cirri, holotype (SIO- BIC A13418). G—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479953/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 17E</figureCitation>
). Pygidium with one pair of small lobed cirriform pygidial cirri ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FC25BCAEFC084788" box="[933,1019,943,970]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long rounded distally (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FB7FBCAEFA96478B" box="[1279,1381,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 18. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). A— close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium. B—ventral view of pygidium with pygidial cirri. C—dorsal view of anterior. D—ventral view of anterior. E—parapodia. F—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; ci, cilia; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479955" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479955/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1032A7733C1C4B33FF47BCD2FE7E4077" blockId="23.[151,1437,259,1438]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FF47BCD2FECC47AF" bold="true" box="[199,319,979,1005]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Variation.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="A0E5AD2E3C1C4B33FEC4BCD5FE7A4077" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3756545320" collectionCode="SIO-BIC" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" specimenCode="A4651" specimenCount="5" typeStatus="paratype">
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1C4B33FEC4BCD5FE4247AC" box="[324,433,980,1006]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Paratypes</typeStatus>
largely match the 
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1C4B33FDFCBCD2FD1147AF" box="[636,738,979,1005]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1C4B33FC9BBCD5FC8847AC" box="[795,891,980,1006]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">paratype</typeStatus>
<collectionCode id="769C3FB63C1C4B33FC01BCD2FC1547AF" box="[897,998,979,1005]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">SIO-BIC</collectionCode>
<specimenCode id="402B0F083C1C4B33FC6BBCD2FBC447AC" box="[1003,1079,979,1006]" collectionCode="SIO-BIC" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">A4651</specimenCode>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FBDABCD5FB2247AF" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1114,1233,979,1006]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FBDABCD5FB2247AF" box="[1114,1233,979,1006]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FB57BCD5FAE147AC" box="[1239,1298,980,1006]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a juvenile (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FF20BCF6FEF54053" box="[160,262,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-25@24.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides kathyae n. sp. A—dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). B—ventral view of holotype, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). C—live dorsal view, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). D—whole body, paratype (SIO-BIC A4651). E—drawing of compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). F—dorsal cirri, holotype (SIO- BIC A13418). G—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A13418). Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479953/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 17D</figureCitation>
), has less segments and is smaller than the 
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1C4B33FD5BBCF6FCB24053" box="[731,833,1015,1041]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
. This specimen was not sequenced but the morphology matches the 
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1C4B33FEA3BB1AFE7A4077" box="[291,393,1051,1077]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5897F4F83C1C4B33FF47BB3EFE8D4117" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1032A7733C1C4B33FF47BB3EFE8D4117" blockId="23.[151,1437,259,1438]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FF47BB3EFEC8401B" bold="true" box="[199,315,1087,1113]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FEC2BB3EFD9C401B" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,623,1087,1113]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FEC2BB3EFD9C401B" box="[322,623,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Galapagomystides kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FDF6BB41FD414018" box="[630,690,1088,1114]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically most like 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FC7EBB41FB84401B" authorityName=", Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[1022,1143,1088,1114]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FC7EBB41FB84401B" box="[1022,1143,1088,1114]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">G. aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FB2DBB41FAA9401B" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1197,1370,1087,1114]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FB2DBB41FAA9401B" box="[1197,1370,1087,1114]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FAE1BB41FA6F4018" box="[1377,1436,1088,1114]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having segment 1 dorsally fused to the prostomium. However, in the phylogenetic analyses, 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FB31BB65FAD9403F" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1201,1322,1123,1150]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FB31BB65FAD9403F" box="[1201,1322,1123,1150]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FAB0BB65FA98403C" box="[1328,1387,1124,1150]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was the sister group to 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FEE7BB89FE1240E3" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Blake and Hilbig" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[359,481,1160,1186]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verenae">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FEE7BB89FE1240E3" box="[359,481,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">G. verenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1C4B33FE6FBB86FDC640E3" box="[495,565,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1408,279,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-61@7.[177,1411,273,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Maximum Likelihood (ML) tree generated from the concatenation of mitochondrial (COI 16rRNA) and nuclear genes (18S rRNA, 28S rRNA). Numbers on nodes represent ML bootstrap values (above node) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (below node). Values below 50% for ML and 0.70 for posterior probabilities are not shown. ‘*’ indicates G. aristata as the type species of Galapagomystides." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479921/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FDC9BB86FC8440E3" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[585,887,1159,1185]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FDC9BB86FC8440E3" box="[585,887,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Galapagomystides kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FCFEBB89FC4940E0" box="[894,954,1160,1186]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was found at both the North 
<collectingCountry id="689AE7E33C1C4B33FA80BB86FAD440E3" box="[1280,1319,1159,1185]" name="Fiji" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fiji</collectingCountry>
Basin and Lau Back-arc Basin, separated by 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1C4B33FD9DBBAAFD714087" box="[541,642,1195,1221]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1099999999999999" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="km" value="1110.0">1110 km</quantity>
. The single specimen collected from the Lau Back-arc Basin does not have a DNA sequence but was morphologically like the 
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1C4B33FC8BBBCEFC8240AB" box="[779,881,1231,1257]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">holotype</typeStatus>
. The distinguishing morphological characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FF35BBF5FEDD414F" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[181,302,1267,1294]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FF35BBF5FEDD414F" box="[181,302,1267,1294]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FEB4BBF5FE83414C" box="[308,368,1268,1294]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are a wide prostomium and elongated dorsal cirri originating from the second segment having a marked 90° angle distal to the body. The chaetal blades of 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FCA1BA19FC694173" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[801,922,1303,1330]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FCA1BA19FC694173" box="[801,922,1303,1330]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FC20BA19FC2F4170" box="[928,988,1304,1330]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are thin and appear delicate, originating from a pointed joint.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5897F4F83C1C4B33FF47BA5EFA7A41DF" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1032A7733C1C4B33FF47BA5EFA7A41DF" blockId="23.[151,1437,259,1438]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FF47BA5EFEBD413B" bold="true" box="[199,334,1375,1401]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1C4B33FED5BA5EFD77413B" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[341,644,1375,1401]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1C4B33FED5BA5EFD77413B" box="[341,644,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Galapagomystides kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1C4B33FD0CBA61FD3B4138" box="[652,712,1376,1402]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is named after the lead author’s mother, Kathy Reimer-Pearson, for her invaluable love and support, and who sparked the lead-author’s interest and enthrallment in invertebrates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
